WEBVTT

00:07:56.011 --> 00:08:01.002
like, "Sounds good,
but that's kind of a big system.

00:08:01.026 --> 00:08:05.577
It's smaller than
a honking-big MRI machine,

00:08:05.601 --> 00:08:06.951
monster MRI machine,

00:08:06.975 --> 00:08:09.140
but can you do something
to shrink it down?"

00:08:10.038 --> 00:08:11.822
And the answer is:

00:08:11.846 --> 00:08:13.016
of course.

00:08:13.040 --> 00:08:16.660
We can replace each
big element in that system

00:08:16.684 --> 00:08:18.279
with a smaller component --

00:08:18.303 --> 00:08:20.200
a little integrated circuit,

00:08:20.224 --> 00:08:24.363
a display chip the size
of a child's fingernail.

00:08:25.451 --> 00:08:27.006
A bit about my background:

00:08:27.030 --> 00:08:33.265
I've spent the last two decades
inventing, prototype-developing